  "lock_statement": "Finite systems must make preservation selections, but personhood itself cannot be selected away. Persons are recoverable centers of safe, sovereign participation, not disposable variables within a viability optimization function. Legitimate governance may allocate resources, manage burdens, constrain harmful actions, and assess risks, but it may never preserve system viability by rendering persons non-persons."
}
